text.section:
The value of motor vehicles, radios, and light bars shall be depreciated over a 5-year period beginning on the date the equipment was put in service as follows:
after 1 year, the equipment shall be valued at 80% of its initial cost;
after 2 years, the equipment shall be valued at 60% of its initial cost;
after 3 years, the equipment shall be valued at 40% of its initial cost;
after 4 years, the equipment shall be valued at 20% of its initial cost; and
after 5 years, the equipment shall be considered to have no remaining value for purposes of this section.
